  <!-- FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" style="background:var(--straw);">
    <div class="section">
      <p class="section-label">Questions?</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">Exterior Care <em>FAQs</em></h2>
      <div class="faq-container" data-aos="fade-up">
        <div class="faq-item" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="0">
          <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
            <span class="faq-question">How often should gutters be cleaned?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Twice a year is standard for most Front Range properties — once in late spring and again after fall leaf drop.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="100">
          <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
            <span class="faq-question">Can power washing damage siding or wood?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Used incorrectly, yes. We adjust pressure and technique by surface — siding, deck wood, and stone all need different settings, which is part of why this is best left to a pro.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item" data-aos="fade-up" data-aos-delay="200">
          <button class="faq-trigger" aria-expanded="false">
            <span class="faq-question">Do you repair wood rot or just identify it?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <p>Both. We can handle minor to moderate trim and siding repairs directly, and we'll flag anything that needs more extensive replacement.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

